{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"FAIL\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P2\",\"location\":\"src/lib/csv.ts:18\",\"description\":\"CSV formula neutralization still omits leading LF (`\\\\n`) from the dangerous-prefix set. A cell beginning with LF followed by a formula marker is only RFC-quoted, not apostrophe-prefixed, while LF is commonly treated as a CSV-injection prefix alongside tab/CR. P2-B is resolved, P3-C is resolved, and I agree P2-A can be deferred because the UI already renders `JSON.stringify(log.payload)` and the admin logs API returns the same raw payload to space admins.\",\"recommendation\":\"Add `\\\"\\\\n\\\"` to `FORMULA_INJECTION_PREFIXES` and add a regression test for a value like `\\\"\\\\n=SUM(1)\\\"` expecting the apostrophe prefix inside the quoted field.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":true},{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\"verification\",\"description\":\"Focused test execution was attempted but this read-only environment still fails before running tests with `Error: spawn EPERM` while loading `vitest.config.ts`.\",\"recommendation\":\"Keep relying on the reported local full Vitest pass for gating, or rerun `npm test -- src/lib/csv.test.ts src/components/dashboard/csv-export.test.ts` in a normal writable/dev environment after the LF-prefix fix.\",\"defer\":true,\"deferRationale\":\"Environment-only verification blocker; not a product defect in the reviewed code.\",\"fixNow\":false}]}"}}
